<HEADLINE> Famous HK Businessman on Future of Hong Kong (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Meanwhile, continuous efforts should be made to promote
multi-lateral economic cooperation between Hong Kong and other
countries and regions, to continue to ensure Hong Kong's leading
role in the economic integration in the Asia-Pacific region," he
added.
</P>
<P>
He said that during the past 17 years, the relationship of
mutual complementarity and benefits between Hong Kong and the
interior area has exerted a profound influence on Hong Kong's
development.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, Hong Kong must continue to seek the support of
the interior area in order to maintain its economic prosperity
and stability," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He explained that a brilliant economic situation in the
interior area will provide the strongest guarantee for Hong
Kong's development, and the strategy of developing central and
western China will broaden the developing space for Hong Kong's
industrial and commercial circle.
</P>
<P>
"Moreover, continuous improvement of the market economic
structure in the interior will add harmony to our cooperation in
the fields of finance, trade and investment, tighten our economic
ties, and strengthen our market links," he said.
</P>
<P>
He finally expressed his conviction that beyond 1997 the
concept of "one country, two systems" would be successfully
realized in Hong Kong, which would make Hong Kong still more
stable and prosperous. 
</P>
