<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Famous HK Businessman on Future of Hong Kong (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- A Hong Kong tycoon said in Beijing
today that in order to maintain and promote economic stability and
prosperity, Hong Kong should preserve its advantages as a global
economic metropolis, and seek continuous support from the interior
area.
</P>
<P>
Tsui Tsin Tong, one of the top 25 men of wealth in Hong Kong,
made this remark at the Second Plenum of the Fifth Session of the
Eighth Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC)
National Committee, of which he is a Standing Committee member.
</P>
<P>
He said that at present Hong Kong enjoys public stability and
economic prosperity, and a smooth transition is gradually turning
into reality.
</P>
<P>
"Beyond 1997, Hong Kong will enter a new phase of development,"
he noted. "It has posed a new challenge for Hong Kong to find a
way to maintain and consolidate its status as an international
centre of trade, finance, shipping, information, and tourism,
while promoting a rapid economic growth in the interior area to
achieve mutual prosperity."
</P>
<P>
As an international free port, Hong Kong has conspicuous
advantages and characteristics of a global economic metropolis,
which should be well preserved to ensure the region's stability
and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
After 1997, Hong Kong should continue to make every effort to
draw all sorts of foreign capital, and provide substantial legal
protection and support for every foreign investor that runs
business in accordance with the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region, he suggested.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
