<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PLA Delegation to NPC Holds Discussion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 5 (Xinhua) -- China's top army officers today
stressed that the People's Liberation Army (PLA) should rally more
closely around the Party Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the
core.
</P>
<P>
General Fu Quanyou and General Yu Yongbo, respectively Chief of
the General Staff and Director of the General Political Department
of the PLA, made the point at a group discussion of the PLA
delegation to the National People's Congress (NPC), which was
attended by General Liu Huaqing, member of the Standing Committee
of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist
Party of China and Vice Chairman of the Central Military
Commission.
</P>
<P>
General Fu said the army should unswervingly keep in unison
with, safeguard the authority of, and follow the command of, the
CPC Central Committee and the Central Military Commission with
Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
He called on the army to hold high the great banner of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, adhere to the basic line
of the Party, put into effect Deng Xiaoping's thought on building
the army in the new period and Jiang Zemin's expositions on army
building, improve the capability of the army, and implement the
strategic concept of "one country, two systems."
</P>
<P>
General Yu said this year is a very important one in the
history of the development of the Party and the country.
</P>
<P>
He called on the army to carry forward at Deng's behest, hold
high the banner of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics, more steadfastly safeguard and follow the
leadership of the Party Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the
core, and more conscientiously keep in unison with the Party
Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
This, he said, will serve as the most important political guarantee to
launch the great cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics into the next century, and the most important
political foundation for increasing unity and stability in the
army. 
</P>
</TEXT>
