<HEADLINE> Bradley Retains WBO Title With Draw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Lonnie Bradley fought back in
the 12th and final round to strive a draw against Otis Grant and
retain his World Boxing Organization middleweight title in Las
Vegas on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
One judge gave Bradley the edge 115-113 while another favored
Grant by the same score, and the third scored it 114-114.
</P>
<P>
There were no knockdowns and neither the American fighter was
ever hurt or in danger of going down.
</P>
<P>
Bradley, 28, is now 25-0-1, with 19 knockouts. Grant, 29, is
28-1-1, with 16 knockouts.
</P>
<P>
Bradley is scheduled to defend his title against John Cornelius
Carr in May in London. 
</P>
