<HEADLINE> EU Makes New Effort to Increase Food Exports to Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) Farm
Commissioner Franz Fischler and a senior trade delegation headed
by him will make a visit to Japan from March 6 to 11 in an effort
to widen Japan's food market for the EU.
</P>
<P>
The Commission said today that this is the first time for an EU
Commissioner of Agriculture to be engaged in this type of activity.
</P>
<P>
Fischler said he had taken the initiative to highlight the need
for food companies to become more active in the promotion and
development of export markets in particular for high quality value
added products.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Fischler and his delegation made up of 19
senior executives of EU food companies will hold discussions with
the Japanese authorities and a wide range of organizations.
</P>
<P>
The trip will culminate in the opening of EU stand at the
Foodex'97 exhibition on March 11th in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
Japan already represents an important food and drinks export
market for the EU with an import of over 3 billion Ecus (about
3.45 billion U.S. dollars) from the union each year.
</P>
<P>
Five key sectors have been selected for this mission including
dairy products, meat and meat products, wines and spirits, certain
horticultural products and olive oil, the Commission said. 
</P>
