<HEADLINE> N. Mogadishu Religious Leader Reinstated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Sheikh Ali Dhere, the
dismissed religious leader in North Mogadishu, has been
reinstated as the chairman of the Supreme Islamic Penal Court.
</P>
<P>
This was announced here today by Prof. Ali Mohamed Gedi, the
spokesman for the Chairing Committee of the Conflict Solving
Conference within North Mogadishu Communities.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Ali Dhere was relieved of his chairmanship position in
the Supreme Islamic Penal Court of North Mogadishu last October
when North Mogadishu faction leader Ali Mahdi Mohamed issued a
decree reshuffling the whole Islamic legislation. Sheikh Ali
Dhere dismissed the decree as illegitimate.
</P>
<P>
The decree has since led to armed confrontations between the
supporters of the two leaders in North Mogadishu and all
the Islamic courts in the city has been paralyzed.
</P>
<P>
Instability has also increased in North Mogadishu where
thieveries and armed banditry have returned back to the streets.
