<HEADLINE> Clinton Calls for Ban on Selling Guns to Foreigners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 5 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
today urged Congress to pass a bill making it illegal for
non-immigrant foreigners to carry or buy firearms and announced
that new proof-of-residency requirements for legal aliens buying
guns under current law.
</P>
<P>
Clinton made the call less than two weeks after a Palestinian
opened fire on tourists at the Empire State Building in New York
City, killing one people and wounding six before fatally shot
himself.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian had been living in a Florida motel for just
three weeks on a tourist visa before buying a gun there.
</P>
<P>
The new rules Clinton announced in the White House would
require a photo ID plus some other proof, such as utility bills,
that the applicant has been in the country for three months.
</P>
<P>
In today's ceremony, the president also resubmitted to Congress
"cop-killer bullets" legislation preventing the development and
manufacture of armor-piercing ammunition.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the president signed a directive requiring that
all guns carried by federal law enforcement officers be equipped
with child safety locks.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 124,000 federally licensed gun dealers in
operation in the country, selling millions of guns to American
residents. Deaths from street gun-fire and fire-armed robberies
often occur. 
</P>
</TEXT>
