<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Major supermarkets in Swaziland
have complained a remarkable drop in sales due to protestors' blockade
of goods coming in and out of the kingdom, Southern African
Broadcasting Association (SABA) reported today.
</P>
<P>
SABA quoted Radio Swaziland as saying that supermarkets in Mbabane,
the capital of Swaziland, are the worst affected by the blockade
sponsored by the Swaziland Federation of Trade Unions (SFTU) and
