</P>
<P>
The Congress of South African Trade Unions, which is in suport of
SFTU, also reportedly took part in the siege, blocking trucks from
entering and leaving the tiny kingdom at two main border posts with
South Africa.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the OK Supermarkets, one of the biggest
in Mbabane, said earlier that sales in his shop had dropped
by almost 80 percent this week. The fall had been worsened by a
national strike which lasted one month, he added.
</P>
<P>
The SFTU-launched nationwide strike was designed to force King
Mswati III to agree to multi-party democracy and improve working
conditions. enditem

