<HEADLINE> US TV Stations to Switch to All-digital Broadcasting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 5 (Xinhua) -- All TV stations in the United
States can begin the transition from current analog technology to
all-digital broadcasting within the next decade thanks to the
production of a new line of professional television studio
equipment.
</P>
<P>
The new line of television studio equipment that Japan's
Sony Corporation introduced today can produce digital,
high-definition programming, is also regarded as the first major
product introduction for cameras, monitors and related equipment.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Government set an industry-wide standard for digital
broadcasts last December, and later this month, the Government is
going to temporarily assign each of the nation's 1,600 TV stations
a second channel for digital, high-definition television
broadcasts.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that TV stations in the nation's 10 largest
cities have been required to install the new equipment quickly
and begin broadcasting digital programming within one year. And
at least four TV stations around the country are already operating
experimental high-definition systems. 
</P>
