<HEADLINE> Qatar Hails Establishment of Diplomatic Ties With </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Qatar today hailed the
establishment of diplomatic ties with Bahrain, according to a
report by the United Arab Emirates' news agency WAM from the
Qatari Capital Doha.
</P>
<P>
The Qatari cabinet today welcomed an agreement signed by Qatar
and Bahrain to open embassies in either country and stressed the
necessity to boost bilateral relations between the two sides,
WAM said.
</P>
<P>
Qatar and Bahrain agreed Sunday to set aside their
long-standing territorial dispute and establish diplomatic ties, 26
year after the two countries gained independence.
</P>
<P>
The long-time dispute between Qatar and Bahrain is over
territorial water boundaries and a string of islands and reefs, as
well as Zubara in northwestern Qatar, where ancestors of Bahrain's
ruling family lived 200 years ago. The islands are under Bahrain's
control but are claimed by Qatar.
</P>
<P>
Qatar brought the dispute before the Hague-based International
Court of Justice in 1991, while Bahrain insists on a regional
solution. 
</P>
