<HEADLINE> Arafat: Palestinian Tenets Eliminating Israel Annulled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The American Jewish community
here said today that Palestinian President Yasser Arafat informed
community leaders during their meeting that Palestinian tenets no
longer call for elimination of the state of Israel.
</P>
<P>
Arafat, meeting with 11 Jewish leaders before holding talks at
the United Nations, said that the 29 offending paragraphs were
deleted because they were not consistent with the peace accords or
the Oslo agreement, spokesman Howard Squadron for the Jewish
leaders group said.
</P>
<P>
"He said publicly that the offensive paragraphs are not there
and have been annulled and that a Palestinian legal committee was
working on a revised charter," he said.
</P>
<P>
Squadron said the Jewish leaders asked Arafat to direct
communications with the Israeli government and not to ask external
groups like the United Nations, the United States and the European
Community to intervene for support.
</P>
<P>
"We agree that there should not be a resort to external
pressures, but communications should be conducted directly between
the parties. (Arafat) was totally in agreement on that idea, so we
are very much consistent on that idea," Squadron said.
</P>
<P>
Arafat indicated that he would prefer to deal directly with
Israel and the controversial housing project the Israeli
government decided to carry on in east Jerusalem would not have
become a disputing issue if Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu had consulted with him beforehand, Squadron said.
</P>
</TEXT>
