<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak's
upcoming visit to Washington at a crucial stage of the peace
process is of special importance, his political advisor Ossama
el-Baz said here today.
</P>
<P>
It transcends the significance of all previous visits, Baz
said on "Good morning Egypt" T.V. program.
</P>
<P>
The Mideast peace process is now undergoing a crucial phase
because of the "new vision" of Israeli Prime Minister Binyamin
Netanyahu's government which showed readiness to commit itself to
previous agreements but "according to its own way."
</P>
<P>
"We will wait to see Washington's reaction to this and its
vision on activating talks on the Syrian and Lebanese tracks,"
Baz said.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak will make a five-day visit to Washington on March 10
for talks with President Bill Clinton, Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright, Secretary of Defense William Cohen and
congressional leadership.
</P>
<P>
He will also meet with U.S. media institutions and a delegation
of the major U.S.-Jewish organizations.
</P>
<P>
At the end of his visit, Mubarak will fly to Chicago for a
meeting with more than 120 businessmen and investors operating in
the United States.
</P>
<P>
Informed sources in the U.S. capital told the Egyptian MENA
news agency that the Egyptian-U.S. talks will also deal with
developments on the various tracks of the peace process following
the Israeli government's decision to build a Jewish neighborhood
in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will examine a number of proposals on reviving
Syrian-Israeli talks, halted in February last year.
</P>
<P>
A high-ranking official, who spoke on condition of anonymity,
said that drawing more U.S. investments to Egypt, the situations
in Sudan and Iraq, as well as regional security issues, will also
be on the agenda.
</P>
<P>
High-ranking Egyptian officials including Foreign Minister Amr
Moussa are now in Washington preparing for the visit. 
</P>
