<HEADLINE> S.Korea, U.S. Cancel 1997 Team Spirit Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, March 6 (Xinhua) -- South Korea and the United States on
Thursday decided to cancel their annual joint "Team Spirit"
military exercise this year in a gesture to ease tensions on the
Korean peninsula.
</P>
<P>
This is the fourth year in a row that South Korea and the
U.S. have called off this major exercise involving 100,000 army,
navy and air force troops. The war games had been staged annually
since 1976.
</P>
<P>
A South Korean Defence Ministry statement said the decision was
made on the basis of the overall security situation on the Korean
peninsula recently.
</P>
<P>
"The decision to cancel Team Spirit is part of efforts by our
two governments to build confidence and to create an atmosphere
conducive to the reduction of tension on the peninsula," the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
It added the decision would have no impact on the joint defence
system of U.S. and South Korean forces, whose plans of staging
"Foal Eagle" exercise, "Focus Lens" exercise and other joint
military exercises in 1997 will not be changed.
</P>
<P>
The announcement came a day after U.S. and South Korean
officials briefed representatives of the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea in New York on proposed four-way peace talks
aimed at securing a formal peace treaty between the two
Koreas. Another round of talks will take place on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
