<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Several Hong Kong members of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), China's top advisory body, answered questions
at a press conference today.
</P>
<P>
The press conference was organized by the joint press center of
the Fifth Session of the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC)
and the Fifth Session of Eighth CPPCC National Committee.
</P>
<P>
Tsui Sze-man, a renowned figure in Hong Kong's literary and art
circles, talked about Hong Kong people's expressions of grief over
the passing away of Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is to return to the embrace of the motherland and
become a special administrative region of the People's Republic of
China, where policies of "one country, two systems," "Hong Kong
people governing Hong Kong" and "a high degree of autonomy" will
be implemented, he said.
</P>
<P>
The smooth transition, prosperity and stability of Hong Kong
today has been owned to the great concept of "one country, two
systems" put forward by Mr. Deng.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Hong Kong people have also witnessed the great
benefits Mr. Deng's reform and opening up have brought to the
inland people, he said.
</P>
<P>
"That's why Hong Kong people are so grateful to Mr. Deng,"
Tsui said.
</P>
<P>
When asked how to deal with the existing laws of Hong Kong
after China resumes the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong,
Maria Tam Wai-chu, a prestigious lawyer from Hong Kong, said that
Hong Kong's existing laws, except those that contravene the
Basic Law of the Hong Kong SAR, will be kept.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 600 laws and more than 1,000 ordinances in
Hong Kong, all of which will be kept except a dozen or so
and several clauses which will not be kept in accordance with
relevant NPC Standing Committee decisions, she said.
</P>
<P>
Even a few provisions of some laws which are not suitable have
not been repealed, and they will be dealt with by the future Hong
Kong SAR, she said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
