<DOCNO> XIE19970306.0084 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC National Committee Members from HK Meets Press (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
When asked how the Provisional Legislative Council supports the
first chief executive of the HKSAR, Ho Sai-chu, who is a member of
the council, said the council will assist Tung Chee Hwa to do a
still better job with affairs in Hong Kong under the principles of
"one country, two systems", "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong"
and "a high degree of autonomy".
</P>
<P>
Sinc Tung Chee Hwa was elected the first chief executive of the
HKSAR, he has done a great deal of work and won the endorsement
and support of the Hongkong people," Ho said. "We are fully
convinced that the HKSAR government has the capability to maintain
Hong Kong's prosperity and stability."
</P>
<P>
In her comment on Hong Kong's extremely high real estate
prices, Ng Chu Lienfan said Hong Kong's economy is a typical
market economy, and the high prices indicates a big demand.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, she noted, many transnational companies and
Hong Kong residents who migrated overseas have returned as they
regard the city as promising, and their demand for office and
housing spaces have pushed up the prices, which have already been
boosted by Hong Kong's limited land space.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong implement an economic policy of non-interference, she
noted. However, she added, if price hikes run so high as to affect
the banking and financial business, and overall economy, then
appropriate measure of interference by the administrative
department are required.
</P>
<P>
The HKSAR will guarantee press freedom as explicitly defined by
the Basic Law, said Tsui Sze-man.
</P>
<P>
Noting that there is no such a thing as absolute press freedom
in any country or region, he said that freedom should be protected
and restricted by the law.
</P>
<P>
The members all expressed their confidence in Hong Kong's
return to China and the implementation of the concept of "one
country, two systems" in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Tsui Sze-man said the principles and policy of "one country,
two systems", "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" and "a high
degree of autonomy" has laid the foundation for the settlement of
the Hong Kong issue, and the work of the Preparatory Committee for
the Establishment of the HKSAR, the founding of the Election
Committee, and the election of the chief executive and the
60-member Provisional Legislative Council won the trust of the
Hong Kong people.
</P>
<P>
In the views of Sze Cheung Pang, thanks to the set principles
and policies with the powerful support of the motherland, Hong
Kong and the interior areas will surely bring about common
development, and Hong Kong tomorrow will surely still more
thriving and prosperous. 
</P>
</TEXT>
