<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Insurer Writes Big Policy For Export Credit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 6 (Xinhua) -- PICC Property, one of three
subsidiaries of China's biggest insurer, has provided a
Shanghai-based company with a 10.45-million-dollar export credit
guarantee for five container cranes to be sold to Brazil.
</P>
<P>
PICC Property signed the agreement with Zhenhua Port Machinery
Co., Ltd in Shanghai today to insure the company against any
problems with its Brazilian buyer.
</P>
<P>
This is the biggest export credit guarantee ever written in
Shanghai. The Brazilian buyer pays 15 percent down and the balance
over the next eight years.
</P>
<P>
China set up a risk fund for the People's Insurance Company of
China in 1988, to begin the export credit insurance business. The
company has provided a total of five billion dollars worth of
export credit guarantees for Chinese exporters in the past several
years.
</P>
<P>
PICC officials say that the company will begin some new
insurance businesses soon, including investment risk insurance,
and insurance for cash deposits.  
</P>
</TEXT>
