<HEADLINE> Northwest China Trade Talks To Promote East-West Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Trade talks that are expected to
promote cooperation between China's eastern and western regions
are scheduled for early April in Xi'an, the capital of northwest
China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The talks will open on April 3 and are being sponsored by the
Special Economic Zones Office of the State Council, the city of
Shanghai, and the provinces of Shaanxi and Jiangsu.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first time for China to hold such an activity
organized by eastern and western cities and provinces. Chinese and
overseas participants from more than 10 countries and regions are
expected to benefit from trading and investment opportunities
provided by the activities.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi hopes to attract five billion US dollars worth of
overseas investment for 100 infrastructure, machinery,
electronics, chemical, pharmaceuticals, foodstuff, and building
materials projects, during the four-day talks.
</P>
<P>
The province also intends to cooperate with domestic partners
in developing 100 projects, valued at more than 17 billion yuan,
covering the fields of energy, petrochemicals, machinery,
metallurgy, building materials, textiles, foodstuff, sideline
products processing and transportation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
