<HEADLINE> French Minister Optimistic Over HK's Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 6 (Xinhua) -- French Minister for Foreign
Trade Yves Galland said here today that he is "optimistic" about
Hong Kong's future and "I feel everybody is optimistic."
</P>
<P>
The minister arrived here this morning for a brief stay
following an eight-day tour of the Chinese mainland to promote
trade links between Beijing and Paris.
</P>
<P>
When he visited Hong Kong several years ago, he recalled,
people were "worried" about their future.
</P>
<P>
Nowadays, however, the entire community is very confident, he
pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Galland quoted a latest survey as saying 95 percent of French
businessmen in Hong Kong have confidence in the territory and they
are still making investments here.
</P>
<P>
Under the "one country, two systems" policy, a smooth
transition of Hong Kong is foreseeable, he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that after Hong Kong returns to China in mid-1997, it
will be a "gate to business with China."
</P>
<P>
The French minister had met with Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive
of the future Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, and other
local dignitaries during his one-day stay here.  
</P>
