<HEADLINE> China's Armed Forces To Get Life Insurance Benefits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- A special office has been set up
in the Chinese capital to work out laws and rules, and when and
how to provide life insurance benefits for the People's Liberation
Army, China's armed forces.
</P>
<P>
The Central Military Commission, China's top military leading
body, has approved an "insurance office" in Beijing, jointly
founded by the PLA General Political Department, the PLA General
Logistics Department and the PLA General Staff HQ.
</P>
<P>
China will create a special fund through legislation, to help
PLA service personnel and their families receive economic
compensation if they are released from service, wounded, or killed
in the line of duty, or for later in life.
</P>
<P>
The office will be under the leadership of the Central Military
Commission and the three departments.
</P>
<P>
The life insurance system to be introduced into the PLA is
considered a special social welfare policy to maintain stability
and order among the troops and to protect their rights and
interests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
