<HEADLINE> Chinese Industrial Zone Benefitting From Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The Songjiang Industrial Zone,
one of nine industrial development zones in Shanghai, has gotten
50 million US dollars in overseas investment in the first two
months of this year by creating a homepage on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
The amount of investment is two times that for the same period
of last year.
</P>
<P>
The industrial zone put its homepage on the Internet last June,
and at least 110,000 people have visited the site located at
http://www.sh.com/zone/sjiz/sjiz.html.
</P>
<P>
Songjiang's homepage visitors can learn about the local
investment environment via the main menu, and can get in touch
with it through E-mail.
</P>
<P>
Other industrial zones in Shanghai are said to be applying for
their own homepages on the Internet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
