<HEADLINE> Rebels Killed In Eastern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 6 (Xinhua) -- More than 160 Tamil rebels were
killed and a large number of others injured this morning when they
attacked the Vavunativu Army detachment in Eastern Province of Sri
Lanka, according to military sources here.
</P>
<P>
The sources said about 800 Tamil rebels attacked the Army
detachment and reinforcements were rushed to the location.
</P>
<P>
Government troops successfully repulsed the attack, inflicting
heavy casualties on the rebels, they said.
</P>
<P>
They added that the rebel leaders of Patendran and the
Batticaloa region were also among those killed.
</P>
<P>
Forty-eight dead bodies of government troops have also been
recovered.
</P>
<P>
The sources said a number of civilians were also killed or
injured by rebel mortar fire in the Batticaloa Town area.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting for a separate Tamil state
in the north and east of the island country since 1983.  
</P>
