<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Reemployment Program to Benefit Unemployed (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Legislators from China's largest city claimed that Shanghai has
basically solved the problem of re-employment by providing new
jobs for 800,000 of the city's approximately one million laid-off
workers.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Xu Zhiyi, director of the Municipal Economic Commission
of Shanghai, said that the main practice in the city is to set up
service center, provide education and vocational training for the
laid-off, and offered them information on employment.
</P>
<P>
"Most of the laid-off workers have found new jobs in the
service trade, such as commerce, property management, and
community household service," he noted.
</P>
<P>
For northeast China's Liaoning Province, which has one tenth of
the country's large and medium-sized enterprises owned by the
state, the establishment and continuous improvement of an
unemployment insurance system is an effective way in carrying out
the re-employment program.
</P>
<P>
According to Chen Suzhi, deputy director of the Standing
Committee of the Liaoning Provincial People's Congress, more than
95 percent of the employees in the province's state-owned
enterprises have bought the insurance policies.
</P>
<P>
"In the past decade, Liaoning has collected a total of 1.06
billion yuan in unemployment insurance funds, and paid 580 million
yuan," said Chen, adding that most of the money was spent in
unemployment relief, medical care, vocational training and job
brokerage.
</P>
<P>
Since China initiated the re-employment program, 2.43 million
laid-off workers have been given new jobs, statistics indicated.
It is expected that the program will help create job opportunities
for another 2.5 million laid-off people this year.
</P>
<P>
However, there are still 10 million surplus workers in China's
state-owned industry, and situation remains stark for
re-employment of the laid-off.
</P>
<P>
During a panel discussion with legislators from southwest
China's Sichuan Province, Labor Minister Li Boyong said that
governments at all levels and enterprises across the country
should attach importance to the re-employment program, and work
out policies to guarantee and promote the progressing of the
program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
