as it declined by 65 cents to close at five dollars. Pengkalen
fell by 49 cents to end at 1.36 dollars, while OUE and the Thai
Prime Fund lost 30 cents each to finish at 6.8 Singapore dollars
and 10.10 US dollars respectively.  
