<HEADLINE> Philippine Military Accuses Rebels of Provocation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Manila, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine military today
accused Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) rebels of provoking
renewed hostilities in Buldon, Maguindanao Province in the
southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Noel Detoyato, spokesman of the Army's 6th Infantry Division,
said the rebels Wednesday fired three rounds of 81mm mortar shells
near the 39th Infantry Battalion's position in Barangay Karigaya,
Buldon.
</P>
<P>
He said MILF rebels also fired mortar shells at Army troopers
in Barangay Daguma, Bagumbayan, Sultan Kudarat Province the other
day.
</P>
<P>
So far no casualties were reported on both sides from the two
said attacks.
</P>
<P>
Detoyato called the attacks part of the rebel's campaign to
drive the soldiers out of the areas where government projects are
being constructed.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that government troops will maintain a defensive
position in spite of the attacks in observance of a local truce
earlier forged by the military and the MILF.
</P>
<P>
The government is presently negotiating peace with the MILF
after talks with the Moro National Liberation Front succeeded last
year.  
