<HEADLINE> Dhaka, Manila to Invigorate Joint Trade Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh and the Philippines today
agreed to invigorate the Joint Committee on Trade (JCT) in a bid
to identify the sectors for expansion in mutual trade and
investment.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached at a meeting today between
Bangladeshi Commerce and Industry Minister Toafel Ahmed and his
Filipino counterpart, Cesar Bautista, who is accompanying
President Fidel Ramos on his visit here.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers discussed possibilities of increasing trade
between the two countries and stressed the need for frequent
exchange of delegations at both official and business levels.
</P>
<P>
Currently trade between the two countries is at a low level
although Bangladesh enjoys a trade surplus by exporting jute goods
and some traditional items, according to Bangladeshi officials.
</P>
<P>
The date of the next meeting of the JCT, which last met in
1989, is yet to be fixed.  
</P>
