<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People in Northeast China Becoming Star Gazers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, March 6 (Xinhua) -- More people in Harbin, the capital
of Heilongjiang Province, have taken an interest in the Hale-Bopp
comet, which comes around every 3,000 years and has become
brighter recently.
</P>
<P>
Since mid-Feburary, residents in most parts of Heilongjiang
have been able to see the comet without the aid of a telescope. At
3:00 a.m., many people get up to get a look at it, with many of
them driving to the suburbs to escape the glare of city lights.
</P>
<P>
The Harbin Planetarium has more than 100 amateur star-gazers
every weekend who are shown video tapes on astronomy, and who
trace the movement of the comet and discuss comets.
</P>
<P>
The appearance of Hale-Bopp will coincide with a total solar
eclipse on March 9 in the province's Mohe County, a scene that
will not happen again for thousands of years, and many local
people are interested in watching it.
</P>
<P>
The number of people attending the planetarium's training
classes has doubled and it has been holding an exhibition on the
total solar eclipse and the comet.
</P>
<P>
The city's amateur star gazers have also opened a hotline to
answer questions on the solar eclipse and the comet, and the city
is planning a "popular science week", a winter camp, and a photo
contest for the solar eclipse. The city has also prepared about
100,000 solar eclipse observation cards for its people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970306.0122 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Development of Shipbuilding Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- China should accelerate the
development of its shipbuilding industry to make it a growth area
in the national economy.
</P>
<P>
Wang Rongsheng, General Manager of China National Shipbuilding
Corp., made the call when attending the current session of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, China's top advisory body.
</P>
<P>
Shipbuilding has the potential to become another rising growth
area in the national economy, just like the electronics,
information and building industries, he said.
</P>
<P>
Shipbuilding industry is a capital-, technology- and
labor-intensive industry, and its development will bring along
that of many other industries, Wang pointed out.
</P>
<P>
He noted China's shipbuilding industry enjoys advantages such
as a mature production structure and well-developed technologies,
and adoption of international practices in operation, marketing,
technical standards and production management.
</P>
<P>
However, he say problems exist. While the production capacity
of large shipyards is less than sufficient, that of medium and
small ones is excessive, he said. What is needed, he said, is
economies of scale.
</P>
<P>
To fuel the development of shipbuilding, its status as a
leading industry must be set, more funds should be instilled for
updating equipment and facilities, and special funds should be
appropriated into research and development.
</P>
<P>
Experts have predicted a demand peak over the next 15 years,
with annual demand ranging from 35 million to 45 million dwt
worldwide, Wang pointed out, adding this will provide historical
opportunities for China's shipbuilding industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
