<HEADLINE> HK Film Festival Marks 50 Years of HK Cinema </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The forthcoming Hong Kong
International Film Festival (HKIFF) will present some 40 local
films spanning from the 1940's to the 1990's in the Hong Kong
cinema retrospective section.
</P>
<P>
From the postwar years to nowadays, the Hong Kong cinema has
gone through hard times and experienced the golden ages, a
spokesman for the festival said here today.
</P>
<P>
With the theme being "fifty years of electric shadow", the
review will feature over 40 excellent films which are chosen from
over 5,000 produced over the period.
</P>
<P>
Immediately following the screenings from March 25 to April 9,
a three-day conference on local cinema will be held, with
participants including some 60 film-makers, industry insiders,
critics and scholars from Hong Kong and beyond.
</P>
<P>
The conference will touch upon the operations of the Hong Kong
film industry, Hong Kong cinema abroad, and historical and
cultural studies of local cinema.
</P>
<P>
Other programs for the HKIFF, organized by the Urban Council,
include global images, director in focus, documentaries, archival
treasures and animation.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 films coming from 42 countries and regions are
expected to be presented during the festival.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
