<HEADLINE> Work on Tibet-Sichuan Highway Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, March 6 (Xinhua) -- A revamping project for a major
highway on the Tibet-Qinghai Plateau, the "roof of the world",
began Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The central government is spending over 400 million yuan (48
million US dollars) on the project, whose goal is to bring a
400-kilometer section of the highway up to a Grade-three national
road. The section connects Lhasa, the regional capital, with the
region's Nyingchi Prefecture.
</P>
<P>
Listed as a key project in the State's Ninth Five Year Plan
(1996-2000), the project is expected to take four years to
complete.
</P>
<P>
The reconstruction work is believed to be of vital importance
to the economic and social growth of eastern Tibet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
