<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India, Pakistan to Resume Talks: Official Sources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The foreign secretaries of India
and Pakistan will meet here on March 28 to resume their official
dialogue on "all issues of mutual concern" aimed at normalization
of relations between the two countries, official sources said here
today.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan Foreign Secretary Shamshad Ahmed is scheduled to
arrive here on March 28 for "comprehensive" talks with his Indian
counterpart, Salman Haider, the Press Trust of India quoted the
sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The foreign secretary-level talks between India and Pakistan
were suspended in January 1994.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, outgoing Pakistan High Commissioner Riaz Khokhar
reportedly disclosed the schedule of the talks to an Indian
newspaper before leaving here for his new assignment as
Islamabad's envoy to Washington.
</P>
<P>
Khokhar also said Pakistan Foreign Minister Gohar Ayub Khan
might send a letter to his Indian counterpart, I. K. Gujral today
or tomorrow on the talks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
