<HEADLINE> Syria Exports 900,000 Tonnes of Cereals in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Syria has exported 900,000 tonnes
of cereals in 1996, earning the country 179 million U.S. dollars,
a government announcement said here today.
</P>
<P>
Syria has over the past few years developed a great deal in
producing foodstuffs, and turned from a food-importing country to
a country of not only self sufficiency, the announcement said.
</P>
<P>
Syria has also grown into a cereal-exporting state, although
several years ago it used to import 1- million-dollar worth of
wheat, barley and flour annually to meet the needs of its
population.
</P>
<P>
By virtue of its high quality cereals, Syria has managed to
find its way into many markets in Europe, Asia and Africa. Syrian
cereals have been highly welcome in the markets of India, Turkey,
Cyprus, Italy, Egypt, Algeria, Tunisia, Morocco and Jordan, it
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
