Last year, the group's profits before taxes rose 20.5 percent
and its total assets reached more than 980 billion HK dollars
(130.6 billion US dollars), registering increase of 6.4 percent
over 1995.
</P>
<P>
On Hong Kong's economic situation, he said that Hong Kong's
status as an international financial center has been greatly
strengthened in the past few years.
</P>
<P>
He said that Hong Kong's economy is on steady growth with the
Hong Kong dollar maintaining sustained stability, property and
stock markets full of vitality, and foreign exchange funds on
increase.  
