the Moldovan Parliament, reports reaching here said today.
</P>
<P>
Motpan Wednesday replaced his predecessor Peter Luchinsky, who
was elected Moldovan president last December and took office on
January 15.
</P>
<P>
Among the votes cast by 76 legislators in the 104-seat
parliament, Motpan won 55 votes. Only a simply majority is needed
to win the election.
</P>
<P>
Legislators from opposition parties boycotted Wednesday's
voting.
</P>
<P>
Motpan, 57, was elected member of parliament in 1990. He won a
re-election in 1994 and has acted as deputy parliament speaker
since then. 
