<HEADLINE> Tanzania Appeals For Help To Resettle Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania has appealed to
the donor community for helping resettle refugees from Zaire and
Burundi in Kigoma Region located in western Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The appeal was made in Kigoma on Wednesday by Tanzania
Principal Secretary in the Prime Minister's Office Ben Moses when
meeting with a delegation of ambassadors and representatives of
the U.N. system who are on an on-the-spot assessment tour.
</P>
<P>
Moses said Tanzania has given sanctuary to refugees but need
assistance to resettle them, adding that the refugees inflow has
caught the authorities unprepared and therefore they could not
finance the operation.
</P>
<P>
About 1,000 to 1,500 refugees are now being received at the
Port in Kigoma every day.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, United Nation High Commissioner for Refugees
(UNHCR) Representative in Kigoma John Adu said UNHCR is sending
Zairean refugees to Lugufu camp, in which about 25,000 refugees
are accommodated there.
</P>
<P>
Most of the refugees came from Fizi area in eastern Zaire
where the Zairean army is pitted against rebel forces.
</P>
<P>
The powerful delegation of high-ranking officials from
embassies based here was led by U.N. Development Program (UNDP)
Representative Victor Angelo.
</P>
<P>
UNICEF Representative to Tanzania Agness Aidoo and World Food
Program Country Director Lacy are among members of the
delegation.
</P>
<P>
