<HEADLINE> Macao Sets up Body to Care for Increasing Diabetes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 6 (Xinhua) -- A special body was established in
Macao Wednesday to care for the increasing number of diabetes
patients, which is expected to reach 41,000 by the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Macao Diabetes Association said that the
association will provide a wide range of services for patients and
local residents.
</P>
<P>
Those services will include hotline service, consulting,
giving out handouts, lectures on ways of preventing the
diseases and medical checkups.
</P>
<P>
Experts said the number of diabetes has increased sharply over
the past decade in Macao, which has an estimated 25,000,000
diabetes patients, or some six percent of its population.
</P>
<P>
Worldwide, 110 million people were found contracted with
the disease in 1994, and that number may grow to 240 million by
the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
Doctors said that currently there is no way to root out the
disease, but it can be eased and prevented by altering bad living
habits.
</P>
<P>
"Diabetes is the cost of social development," said a local
doctor at a press conference Wednesday. "But the possibility of
contracting the disease can be drastically lowered if you
exercise more and are careful of your diet."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
