<DOCNO> XIE19970306.0169 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Expert Calls for Attention to Population Aging </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- A population expert said today in
Beijing that the government should pay close attention to the
problem of population aging, and take appropriate measures to
prepare for the arrival of a gerontological society.
</P>
<P>
Wu Cangping, a professor with the institute of population
theories of the People's University of China, one of the country's
leading academies, made this remark at the third plenum of the
Fifth Session of the Eighth National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
Predicting that the number of aged people will reach 130
million, or one tenth of the population, by the end of the
century, Wu said that China will soon enter a gerontological
society.
</P>
<P>
"The aging of population has posed a grave and urgent challenge
to China, a large country with comparatively backward economy and
culture," he warned. "This will affect our country's sustainable
development if no adequate measure are taken promptly."
</P>
<P>
Above all, efforts should be made to enhance the awareness of
the aging problem among the entire people, especially among
decision-makers and the middle-aged and young citizens, he said.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that the government move promptly to turn the
State Family Planning Commission into a "state population
commission," and regard the work concerning population aging as
one of its tasks.
</P>
<P>
"We must not miss the opportunity to make full preparations for
the aging of the population, which should cover the aspects of
thinking and theories, legislation and renovation of systems, and
materials, institutions and talents," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that new programs including social gerontology,
geriatrics, and geriatric nursing and psychology be set up in
higher education institutes to prepare talented personnel for the
need of the next century.
</P>
<P>
In order to maintain the physical and mental health of senior
citizens, he said, a medical insurance system should be gradually
set up and perfected in both urban and rural areas, and a
nationwide fitness campaign be launched and promoted across the
country.
</P>
<P>
"By means of strengthening health care education for the entire
population, especially for the aged citizens, we can help more
people to enter and live their old age in good health and
achieve longevity," he claimed.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the necessity to provide adequate economic
guarantees for aged people both in the cities and the countryside
with a pension insurance system that has the widest coverage.
</P>
<P>
"We should set up a kind of social mechanism, under which the
aged people can enjoy the fruits of social progress, and try to
fix it through legislation," he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
