<HEADLINE> Light Industrial Output Registers Ups and Downs in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The latest statistics from the
State Satistics Bureau show that the output of major light
industrial products registered ups and downs for different
categories in January.
</P>
<P>
The country produced 1.98 million bicycles in January, down
27.3 percent from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The output of sewing machines and color television sets was
517,800 and 2.25 million, respectively, up 2.8 percent and 17.2
percent.
</P>
<P>
The country also manufactured 2,57 million radios and 1.2
million household washing machines, up 17.2 percent and 30.7
percent, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
