<HEADLINE> Output of Chemical Fibers Reports Ups and Downs in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The latest statistics from the
State Satistics Bureau show that the country turned out 944,200
tons of chemical fibers in January, down 2.3 percent form the same
period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The output of synthetic fibers stood at 277,500 tons, up 21.9
percent.
</P>
<P>
That of viscose fibers was 654,500 tons, down 10.1 percent.
</P>
