<HEADLINE> Profits of State-Owned Industry Increase in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The latest statistics released by
the State Statistics Bureau show that the profits of the
state-owned industry covered by the state budget hit 499 million
yuan in January, up 23.8 percent compared with the same period of
1996.
</P>
<P>
The top three profit makers were Shanghai, Shandong and Henan,
which generated a profit of 207 million yuan, 201 million yuan and
68 million yuan, respectively, in January.
</P>
<P>
The biggest loss was registered in Liaoning Province, amounting
to 236 million yuan. 
</P>
