<HEADLINE> East China's Province Speeds Up Post And Telecom Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Shandong, a coastal province in
east China, plans to invest six billion yuan in post and
telecommunication this year, China Electronic News reported today.
</P>
<P>
The local post and telecom authorities plan to increase 1.15
million lines of program-controled switchboards, add one million
telephone users, increase the number of pager users to 800,000,
and develop a mobile telecom system capable of transmitting
signals for one million subscribers.
</P>
<P>
Both the postal business turnover and income of operators are
expected to break the eight billion yuan mark this year, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Priority will be given to development of mobile
telecommunications, it said. By the end of the year, all cities
above county level, major tourist spots, and towns in the
developed eastern region are scheduled to be hooked up with the
provincial mobile telecom network.
</P>
<P>
The province plans to increase the number of mobile phone users
to 250,000 this year, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
