<HEADLINE> Sichuan to Build Five Expressways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Chengdu, capital of southwest
China's Sichuan Province, will build five expressways and an array
of speedways during the 1996-2000 period, in a bid to ease traffic
congestion.
</P>
<P>
The expressways include Chengdu-Mianyang, Chengdu-Ya'an,
Chengdu-Nannan and a freeway that circles the city. Total length
is estimated at 211 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Chengdu currently is connected with the city of Chongqing, the
industrial heartland in southwest China, by a just-completed
freeway.  
</P>
