<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Aircraft Destroyed, 4 Airmen Killed in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 6 (Xinhua) -- An aircraft was destroyed and four
soldiers were killed this morning when Tamil rebels attacked an
air force base in Trincomalee and the Army's Brigade Headquarters
in Vavunativu in Eastern province of Sri Lanka, according to a
military spokesman here today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that nearly 300 rebels had entered the base
from the rail track and launched mortar and small arms fire
attacks.
</P>
<P>
The air force successfully repulsed the attack by using air and
ground fire, however, an air force transport plane was totally
destroyed and four airmen were killed in the attack, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also said that the rebels' casualties are much more, but the
rebels had removed the dead and injured when they retreated on
arrival of reinforcements.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that in Vavunativu, an 800-meter bridge was
blasted and the Vavunativu Army detachment was attacked with
mortars. The rebels had then directed artillery fire on the
Brigade Headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The bridge has been damaged only in parts and this will not
hamper troops movements, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the attacks starting around 1:30 a.m. today lasted
till dawn.
</P>
<P>
A search operation resulted in the recovery of two suicide
jackets and some weapons with three dead bodies of the rebels, the
spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a guerrilla war for a
separate state in the north-east of the country since 1983.
</P>
</TEXT>
