<HEADLINE> China's Automobile Production, Sales Up in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- China's automobile industry
witnessed upward growth in January, with production reaching
122,000 units, according to a report released today from the
Ministry of Machine-building Industry.
</P>
<P>
The figure represented an increase of 4.8 percent over the same
period last year. Meanwhile, sales nationwide totalled 113,000
units, up 8.51 percent.
</P>
<P>
Of the different models, heavy-duty trucks, mini-trucks, large
buses, and cars scored a growth rate of more than 20 percent in
both production and sales.
</P>
<P>
Cars made the most noteworthy progress. In January, China
produced 39,000 cars, a rise of 32.5 percent, and sold 37,000
units, up 42.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the same month, production and sales of medium- and
light-duty trucks and medium- and light-buses declined.
</P>
<P>
Of the seven key automobile corporations, First Auto Works
Corporation, Shanghai Automotive Industrial Corporation, Tianjin
Automative Industrial Corporation and China National Heavy-duty
Truck Corporation registered increases in both production and
sales. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
