<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Star Skaters to Vie for Golds at Naitonal Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese star skaters, headed by Li
Jiajun, Yang Yang, Wang Chunlu and Zhang Yanmei, will vie for the
gold medals of the short-track speedskating competitions at the
China's Eighth National Games, organizers said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The two-day cometition will produce four gold medals in the
men's and women's 500- and 100-meter races slated on Friday and
Saturday in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
"The gold of the women's 500-meter race will be the first one
at the Nanional Games," Guo Ruijiu, chief of competition section
of the short-track speedskating competition committee, told a
press conference.
</P>
<P>
"Wang Chunlu, Yang Yang, Zhang Yanmei all have the chance to
win the first gold," Guo said.
</P>
<P>
Wang, from Jilin Province, claimed the gold medals of the 500
and 1,000 meters races and the 3,000 relay at the 1995 World
Championships. Yang of Heilongjiang Province shared the 3,000
relay with Wang at the 1995 World Championships and won the 1,500
meters in the Asian Winter Games.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old Zhang, representing the Army, was the 500
meters silver medalist at the 1994 Winter Olympics.
</P>
<P>
The male skaters will be led by Li Jiajun, who won the title of
the 1,000 meters at the world championships last year.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that some of the winter events are
included in the National Games. It is to give the chance to some
provinces such as Jilin and Heilongjiang to further develope the
sports, the organizers said.
</P>
<P>
Other winter events to be held in the upcoming National
Games includes speedskating.
</P>
<P>
Xue Ruihong, ranked first in the World Cup series for the
women's 500-meters this season, will take part in the speedskating
competitions which will be held later this month.
</P>
<P>
Xue now leads the World Cup 500 meters series with 385 points.
Fracziska Schenk of Germany is second.
</P>
<P>
The Eighth National Games will begin on October 7 in Shanghai.
</P>
</TEXT>
