<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangxi Holds Rural Film Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Farmers in South China's Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region enjoyed their first film festival this
past week.
</P>
<P>
During the six-day festival, which opened March 1st in Hengxian
County, more than 20 national films and a series of science and
educational films were exhibited that spoke to the farmers' lives
and were loved by them.
</P>
<P>
One film, titled Liu Hulan, told the story of a well-known
national heroine, who was village-born and devoted her life to
the War of Liberation (1946-1949).
</P>
<P>
The Guangxi farmers have difficulty watching a film due to
their remote dwelling places and the underdeveloped local
economy. The organizers of the festival promised to let every
farmer in Hengxian County, Yulin City and Dahua County, which are the
centers of the festival, enjoy at least one film during the
festival.
</P>
<P>
The local departments concerned are trying to hold various
rural film festivals at irregular intervals in winter when farmers
are not as busy.
</P>
<P>
The festival was co-sponsored by seven organizations, including
the local cultural department and the local committee of
nationality affairs, which will take effective measures against
film smuggling to ensure a prosperous and healthy rural film
market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
