<DOCNO> XIE19970306.0204 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Provincial Party Secretary and His Farmer Friend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- It was late at night, but Dai
Xianlu and Xie Shijie were still immersed in conversation.
</P>
<P>
Dai, a village Party secretary from southwest China's Sichuan
Province, and Xie, Party secretary of the province, are both
deputies to the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC), China's
legislature, which is in its fifth annual session in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
It has become a custom for Dai to talk about farm production in
his county and changes in villages with the provincial party
secretary, who loves to make friends with farmers, whenever they
meet at NPC annual sessions.
</P>
<P>
Offering a citrus to Dai, who was in trim business suits with a
necktie, Xie said humorously: "From what you wear, I can say the
farmers' life is turning better day by day."
</P>
<P>
Dai said that "we farmers have 'three joys' last year, namely,
higher grain output and more income, no more 'IOUs', and no more
mono-culture mode," he listed.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Sichuan province scored good harvests, and the overall
grain output reached a record 47.058 million tons. The average net
income of farmers was 1,453 yuan, a rise of 295 yuan over 1995.
</P>
<P>
Dai recalled that the per capita income in his village rose to
1,600 yuan last year from 1,280 yuan in 1995, while six township
enterprises chopped up an annual output value of 20 million yuan
were set up through fund-raising among the villagers.
</P>
<P>
"Almost all families in our village have built new houses
equipped with new television sets," he added. Some households have
access to telephones service and even cellular phones, or have
bought motorcycles.
</P>
<P>
Xie nodded with smiles, while he was briefed on changes that
have occurred in villages. He praised Dai and his fellow villagers
for the progress they had achieved last year.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, he urged Dai not to be contented but go on
working harder for a still better life and catch up with those
affluent villages in the eastern coastal areas.
</P>
<P>
The village Party secretary acknowledged that last year's good
harvest has resulted in two diversed ideas among the farmers.
</P>
<P>
"Some villagers think that it is easy to have good farm yields
again this year, while some other folks doubt if the grain output
can be increased further," he explained.
</P>
<P>
Noting that both ideas are harmful to agricultural production,
Xie said "we should have no letup in our work, and take more
effective measures to ensure steady farm yields and better
diversified rural economy."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Xie promised that the provincial government will
strive to ease the farmers' burden in accordance with the relevant
policies of the central authorities.
</P>
<P>
"The goal of our province this year is to further increase the
grain output by 500 million kilograms and farmers' per-capita
income by at least 200 yuan," he told Dai. 
</P>
</TEXT>
