<HEADLINE> Japanese Telecom Company to Deepen Cooperation with Jiangsu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Fujitsu, a leading Japanese
telecommunications supplier, held a conference with east China's
Jiangsu Province on February 19, vowing "comprehensive
cooperation" with the province.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest issue of People's Posts and
Telecommunications, representatives with the Japanese company said
that the Fujitsu-Jiangsu cooperation will expand to areas beyond
the telecommunications industry, as both partners adhere to a
reciprocal principle in trading.
</P>
<P>
So far, Fujitsu has established three joint ventures in
Jiangsu, and its manufacturing base extends to four booming
cities, Nanjing, Suzhou, Nantong and Changzhou.
</P>
<P>
The cooperative projects cover the fields of
telecommunications, printer manufacturing, software development,
integrated circuit assembling, and the production of financial
electronic equipment.
</P>
<P>
Negotiation on other cooperative projects are well under
way, the paper said, but gave no further details.  
</P>
