<HEADLINE> Sales Revenue of State-Owned Sector Up in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- China's state-owned industry
covered by the state budget turned out a sales revenue of 172.62
billion yuan in January, up 5.5 percent from that in the same
period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The top three revenue turnovers were Shanghai, Shandong and
Jiangsu.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai realized a sales revenue of 11.32 billion yuan in
January, up 8.2 percent from the figure of January 1966.
</P>
<P>
That of Shandong was nine billion yuan, up 12.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
That of Jiangsu was 8.74 billion yuan, down 1.1 percent.
</P>
