<HEADLINE> Britain Provides Fund to Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The British government has granted
4 million pounds sterling to support the Relief and Rehabilitation
Program (RRP) in Sri Lanka, according to official sources today.
</P>
<P>
The money will be used over the next four years to assist some
200,000 people most affected by the ongoing civil conflict in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The program will concentrate on meeting the needs of women,
children and the most disadvantaged people in society whatever
their ethnic background.
</P>
<P>
The RRP will assist in rebuilding basic infrastructure,
improving access to health services and education and promoting
agricultural production, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
A further contribution of 500,000 pounds sterling has been
agreed to support the work of the International Committee of the
Red Cross in Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Britain provided to Sri Lanka 14.6 million pounds in 1995 and
1996, of which 6.5 million pounds were given through the
Commonwealth Development Corporation.  
</P>
