<HEADLINE> Uganda to Set up Power Stabilizer Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Uganda has started construction
of a power stabilizer plant in capital Kampala, reported The New
Vision daily today.
</P>
<P>
The million-U.S.-Dollar plant will finish its construction
work by the middle of this year when it will assemble, repair and
supply stabilizers to areas affected by power fluctuations such
as east and central Africa.
</P>
<P>
Uganda and Kenya are among the countries which have been hart
hit by power fluctuations, resulting in the damages of TV sets,
radios and refrigerators.
</P>
<P>
Power stabilizers are in short supply in east Africa and the
prices of the imported ones from developed countries are very
expensive.
</P>
<P>
The owner of the plant is electronics dealer Musicraft.
</P>
