<HEADLINE> Malaysian Soldiers Encouraged to Better Themselves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Defense Minister
Syed Hamid Albar said here today that his ministry encouraged the
members of the Malaysian Armed Forces (MAF) to better themselves
academically to enhance the standard of professionalism within the
MAF.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the signing of two memoranda of understanding
(MOUs) between his ministry and two educational institutes, he
said that with better qualification and discipline, members of the
armed forces could provide excellent service to the community.
</P>
<P>
The defense ministry will try to provide more opportunities in
this respect in meeting the demand for skilled manpower in the
professional and technical fields, he said.
</P>
<P>
Syed Hamid did not agree with the belief that the armed forces
would lose more personnel if they were given opportunities to
acquire professional qualifications.
</P>
<P>
"We should not take such a stand because there will be those
still willing to serve," he said, adding the armed forces would
still be proud of those who left the service if they were
successful in their respective careers.  
</P>
