<HEADLINE> Uganda Orders 400M Condoms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Uganda has ordered 400 million
condoms in the next four to six years in attempts to curb
communicable disease and promote family planning, reported the
Crusader paper today.
</P>
<P>
Elizabeth Madra, the commissioner for communicable disease in
Ugandan Health Ministry, was quoted as saying that her ministry
will become the center to supply condoms to all users throughout
the country.
</P>
<P>
Madra noted that condom use in Uganda has tremendously
increased in urban areas. But she did not give figures.
</P>
<P>
She ensured that the condoms will have been examined in modern
laboratories to ensure that they are safe.
</P>
<P>
However, she said the mounting use of condoms has raised the
fear of polluting the environment by burning used ones.
</P>
<P>
Ten million condoms were sold in the eastern African country
last year, a 66 percent growth compared with 5.9 million in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Education on family planning and safe sexual behavior is
spreading to Ugandans nationwide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
