<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Coastal Tianjin Boosting Cooperation with Inland Ningxia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Wide-ranging economic cooperative
projects are on a roll between north China's biggest open coastal
city of Tianjin and the inland Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region in
the northwest.
</P>
<P>
A total of 151 agreements, involving trade, technology, ports,
capital construction and agricultural development have been signed
between the localities.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin is a major port city in north China; Ningxia is a
leading base of natural resources and raw materials. Currently,
more than 80 percent of export goods in Ningxia are shipped
through the Tianjin port.
</P>
<P>
In contrast to its previous practice of providing free
assistance and expecting nothing in return, such as offering
donations to its inland counterpart, Tianjin is now engaging
Ningxia in hopes of benefitting from its potential market and
abundant mineral resources, Tianjin's Executive Vice-Mayor Li
Shenglin said on a recent tour to Ningxia.
</P>
<P>
The two areas are economically complementary in many ways, Li
said.
</P>
<P>
This year, Tianjin will give priority to transferring products,
technology, equipment and information to Ningxia, which in turn
will supply Tianjin with energy, raw materials and labor,
according to Ren Qixing, vice-chairman of the Ningxia Hui
autonomous regional government.
</P>
<P>
Together, the two sides will set up a number of companies
engaged in building materials, chemicals and non-ferrous metals,
and will develop export-oriented agriculture, while Ningxia will
establish agricultural by-products bases for Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will also jointly finance four industrial
projects, valued at about 70 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
To facilitate bilateral economic ties, Ningxia and Tianjin will
set up a special committee to coordinate economic and
technological cooperation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
