<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India's Gold Output Increases Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 6 (Xinhua) -- India's gold production has gone
up by 25 percent to 1,677.48 kilograms during April 1996 to
January 1997, the Times of India said today.
</P>
<P>
The output in the corresponding period last year is 1,347.23
kilograms.
</P>
<P>
India had the largest consumption of gold in the world in 1996.
</P>
<P>
</P>
