<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The first batch of Russian-made
Su-30 fighter planes will join the Indian air force later this
month, the Hindustan Times said today.
</P>
<P>
According to a contract, India will purchase a total of 40
Su-30 fighter planes from Russia at a cost of 70 billion rupees
(about two billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
