<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Agricultural Revenue up 4.8 Percent in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The European Union's agricultural
revenue rose in real terms by 4.8 percent last year to its highest
level in more than 20 years, the European Commission announced
here today.
</P>
<P>
The commission estimated that the total grain output amounted
to 202 million tons in 1996, 27 million tons more than that of the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
Sugar output was 15.66 million tons, equal to the production in
1995 and wine hit 17.4 billion litters, an increase of 2.5 billion
litters from 1995.
</P>
<P>
Due to the "mad-cow" crisis, the output of beef decreased by 4
percent, the commission said. Poultry meat, pork and mutton
increased slightly, it said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a package program for agricultural pricing for
fiscal 1998 has been adopted, which promises to keep the
consistency of the common agricultural policy which started in
1992 and is designed to save 82 million ECUs for 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
