<HEADLINE> Giant Steel-maker Earns ISO Quality Certificate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua)-- The Capital Iron and Steel Corp has
been granted ISO 9002 certification by the China Classification
Society after verification of its quality system, "China Daily"
reported today.
</P>
<P>
ISO 9002 certification is conferred on manufacturers whose
products meet internationally-required standards, awarded by the
China Certification Society, one of the first 10 organizations
approved by the State Technical Bureau and the State Commodities
Inspection Bureau to domestic enterprises, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
"The certification demonstrates that the company's management
has fully complied with international standards and will help our
products to enter the European market and the United States,"
Zhang Yanlin, deputy general manager of the corporation, said.
</P>
<P>
The company is the core enterprise of the Capital Iron and
Steel Group (Shougang Group), one of the 10 giant steel producers
in China.
</P>
<P>
The group plans to export 600,000 tons of steel in 1997, an
increase of 11 percent over last year.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the Shougang Group produced 7.3 million tons of
iron, 7.92 million tons of steel and 7.92 million tons of rolled
steel, earning a profit of 324 million yuan (40 million US
dollars). 
</P>
