<HEADLINE> International Food-ingredient Producers Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua)-- An international conference on
food-ingredient production will be held here from March 10 to 12,
"China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
China's development potential in this sector has drawn many
overseas manufacturers to Food Ingredients China'97 which is aimed
at improving the industry through global exchange, according to
You Xin, president of the China Food Additive Association.
</P>
<P>
More than 30 overseas participants will bring many food
additives, including those China cannot produce. In addition,
finishing food products, equipment and the latest technology will
be displayed by more than 360 exhibitors, You said.
</P>
<P>
China is among the world's top exporters of citric acid and
aginomoto. It also turns out more than 10,000 tons of food
coloring and sweeteners a year, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
However, the country still lags behind the world's top level in
products such as preservatives, thickeners and emulsifiers, which
are necessary to enhance the quality and nutritional value of
certain foods.
</P>
<P>
In spite of its huge food market, China's annual
food-ingredient output value is only 12 billion yuan (1.4 billion
US dollars), compared with 4 billion US dollars in the United
States and 3 billion US dollars in Japan.
</P>
<P>
Co-operation in the food-ingredient and additives sector is
expected to push forward China's food industry, You said. Food is
China's third largest industry after machinery and electronics and
textiles.
</P>
<P>
The show at the Beijing International Exhibition Center is the
seventh of its kind for domestic food additive producers, but the
first time for international counterparts, the paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
