<P>
WASHINGTON, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) today announced that it has approved three loans
totaling 169.6 million U.S. dollars to Uruguay to support its
programs to modernize the central government and strengthen
municipalities in the interior.
</P>
<P>
