<HEADLINE> Czech-Arab Trade Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Trade between the Czech Republic
and Arab countries grew to 461.3 million U.S. dollars in 1996, up
29.6 percent over the previous year, an official said today.
</P>
<P>
Egypt is the Czech Republic's biggest trade partner among the
arab countries, with the two-way trade surpassing 109 million
dollars last year, deputy chairman of the Czech-Arabian Chamber of
Commerce Eduard Gombar told reporters.
</P>
<P>
Czech exports to Egypt amounted to 93.1 million dollars, while
its import from that Arab country accounted for 16.2 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
With the sharp decline in demands from its traditional western
trade partners, the Czech Republic has started to develop trade
with Arab countries. The Czech-Arab trade now accounts for 1
percent of the republic's total foreign trade. 
