<DOCNO> XIE19970306.0246 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Third Plenary Meeting of NPC Fifth Session Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The Fifth Session of the Eighth
National People's Congress (NPC), China's top legislature,
convened its third plenary meeting today to review two draft laws
-- draft amendments to the criminal law and a draft national
defense law -- and other legislative affairs.
</P>
<P>
Chen Muhua, vice-chairperson of the NPC Standing Committee and
an executive chairman of the NPC Fifth Session, presided over
today's session.
</P>
<P>
Wang Hanbin, vice-chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, made
explanations on draft amendments to the criminal law.
</P>
<P>
He said that the existing Criminal Law enacted 17 years ago has
played an important role in cracking down on crimes, safeguarding
national unity and security and social order.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he added, it has also played an important role in
defending the power of the people's democratic dictatorship and
socialist system, and the smooth progress of the cause of
socialism.
</P>
<P>
However, he added, there do exist some problems in the law, and
its revision will represent a major step forward in improving the
country's socialist legal system.
</P>
<P>
The draft amendments expand the Criminal Law to 449 articles
from the existing 192 articles.
</P>
<P>
Chi Haotian, vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission,
State Councillor and defense minister, gave explanations to the
draft national defense law at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The draft, comprising 13 chapters with 76 articles, stresses
the Chinese Communist Party's leadership over the armed forces,
and gives definitions on national defense duties of state organs,
the armed forces, border defense, the defense industry, defense
spending, and military ties with overseas.
</P>
<P>
A draft decision on matters concerning election of deputies to
the Ninth NPC and draft methods for electing Hong Kong deputies to
the Ninth NPC were also submitted to the NPC for deliberation.
</P>
<P>
According to the draft decision, the number of deputies to the
Ninth NPC shall not exceed 3,000, with one deputy elected from
every 220,000 urban residents or every 880,000 rural residents.
The deputies should be elected before the end of January 1998.
</P>
<P>
A special election conference consisting of Chinese citizens in
Hong Kong will be held responsible for the election of 36 deputies
to the Ninth NPC, according to the draft methods.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, as the last item on the agenda, heard explanations
on a motion set forth the State Council on upgrading Chongqing
city in Sichuan province to become a municipality directly under
the central government.
</P>
<P>
State Councillor Li Guixian said the purpose of establishment
of Chongqing municipality is to give full play to its role as an
economic center in southwest China and the upper reaches of
Yangtze river.
</P>
<P>
The proposed municipality will have an area of 82,000 sq km
with a population of 30 million, making it the largest
municipality in China.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2,634 deputies attended today's meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970306.0247 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Draft Law on National Defense Submitted (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- China's first basic law in the
field of national defense today was submitted to the Fifth Session
of the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC), China's
legislature, for deliberation.
</P>
<P>
The draft law on national defense had been discussed twice
by the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
In a bill of joint signatures, Premier Li Peng and President
Jiang Zemin, who is also chairman of the Central Military
Commission (CMC), said that the law was intended to help build and
consolidate national defense, safeguard China's sovereignty,
unity, territorial integrity and safety, and ensure the smooth
development of the socialist modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
They said that the draft law, which was formulated under the
guidance of Mao Zedong's military thinking and Deng Xiaoping's
theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics and
ideas of military building in the new historical period, has
summarized the experience of China's building of national defense,
and is compatible with the demands of national defense and army
building under the circumstances of a socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
Chi Haotian, Vice-Chairman of the CMC, State Councillor and
Minister of National Defense, was authorized by the State Council
and the CMC to explain the draft law to the legislators.
</P>
<P>
"The law covers not only guarding and resistance against any
possible armed invasions from the outside, but also crackdowns on
any domestic armed rebellions or armed riots aimed at splitting
the motherland, subverting state power, and overthrowing the
socialist system," he noted, adding that such armed rebellions and
riots seriously threaten national sovereignty and unity,
territorial integrity and state security.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed the necessity to keep on a high alert against
"Taiwan Independence" and other activities that aim to split the
country.
</P>
<P>
The draft law stipulates that the armed forces of the People's
Republic of China shall be subject to the leadership of the
Communist Party of China, thus providing a legal guarantee for the
principle that "the Party commands the troops."
</P>
<P>
Chi pointed out that it is the successful experience of China's
armed struggle and building of national defense, and a basic
guarantee for the country's political and social stability, ethnic
unity and national security, to adhere to the absolute Party
leadership over the military.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970306.0248 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Draft Law on National Defense Submitted (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Although the Constitution has stipulated the Party's leading
role in the country, it still has great significance to clearly
define the Party's leadership over the armed forces. This is a
principle with Chinese characteristics that must be insisted on,"
he noted.
</P>
<P>
The draft law stipulates that China will carry out a defense
policy of "active defense" and stick to the principle of
"self-defense by the entire people."
</P>
<P>
Chi said that it is a worldwide practice to set forth a
country's policies, basic principles and systems of national
defense by means of legislation.
</P>
<P>
"With the development of reforms, opening up and socialist
modernization drive, China is playing a more important role in
international affairs. However, some hostile forces have
deliberately fabricated the theory of 'China Threat', and tried
every means to damage China's global image," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He said that a law on national defense can clearly illustrate
China's peace-loving principles and policies for national
defense to the rest of the world, and help create a favorable
external environment for the country's reform and opening drive.
</P>
<P>
Drawing experience from other major countries in the world, the
draft law stipulates that the state should guarantee necessary
financial outlay for national defense in accordance with specific
circumstances.
</P>
<P>
It also makes stipulations on the power of relevant government
organs in national defense, national defense assets, education
on national defense, national defense mobilization, and
protection of the servicemen's rights and interests.
</P>
<P>
It suggests that defense affairs in special administrative
regions be decided by the basic laws of the special
administrative regions and other relevant laws.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
