<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Draft Law on Election of HK Deputies Submitted for NPC Deliberation (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The election conference comprises Chinese citizens from the
Election Committee for the first HKSAR government, members of the
Eighth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) who are Chinese citizens of the
HKSAR but are not concurrently members of the Election Committee,
and members of the HKSAR Provisional Legislative Council who are
Chinese citizens.
</P>
<P>
Cao said the 400 members of the Election Committee for the
first HKSAR government has a broad representation in Hong Kong. It
is suitable for the election conference to be based on Chinese
citizens from the Election Committee.
</P>
<P>
Considering the suggestion of most NPC deputies and CPPCC
National Committee members from Hong Kong, he added, the
membership of the election conference has been expanded to include
CPPCC National Committee members among Hong Kong residents who are
not concurrently members of the Election Committee, and Chinese
citizens among members of the Provisional Legislative Council.
</P>
<P>
Cao said the method applies only to election of deputies
to the Ninth NPC from the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
The election procedure stipulated by the draft method is: the
first meeting of the election conference will be called by the NPC
Standing Committee, and the meeting will elect a presidium with 11
conference members. The presidium will preside over the election
conference.
</P>
<P>
The number of candidates should be one-fifth to one half more
than the number of deputies.
</P>
<P>
Election result will be announced by the presidium, and be
reported to the Subcommittee to Examine Deputies' Qualifications
under the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
And the NPC Standing Committee, in accordance with a report by
the Subcommittee, will confirm the qualifications of deputies and
make public the names of deputies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
