<DOCNO> XIE19970306.0257 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chongqing Expected to Become China's Fourth Municipality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing, an industrial city in
southwest China, is expected to become the fourth municipality
after Beijing, Shanghai and Tianjin after the current session of
China's legislature approves a motion submitted today by the State
Council, China's cabinet,
</P>
<P>
In a proposal submitted for approval to the Fifth Session of
the Eighth National Conference (NPC), which has been in session
since last Saturday, Premier Li Peng termed it "an important move
to promote economic and social development in southwest China."
</P>
<P>
In explaining the motion on behalf of the State Council, State
Councillor Li Guixian recalled at the session's third plenary
meeting today Chongqing was designated by the State Council as one
of China's first cities to experiment with economic structuring on
an experimental basis, and granted equal status in the
administration of economy as that of a province in 1983.
</P>
<P>
To give full scope to Chongqing's rule as a major economic
center and further push forward economic and social development in
eastern Sichuan, the southwest China and the entire upper reaches
of the Yangtze River, he said.
</P>
<P>
The State Councillor said the move will also contribute to the
construction and relocation for the gigantic Three Gorges Dam
project which has been under way since 1993 with one million
people to be displaced. Moreover, the move will relieve Sichuan
from managing China's most populous province, covering a large
land area.
</P>
<P>
Li further noted that the conditions for upgrading Chongqing to
become China's fourth municipality are mature.
</P>
<P>
As the largest economic center at the upper reaches of the
Yangtze and a major port city with close overseas contact, he
said, it is also a center of communications, scientific and
technological, cultural and education in southwestern China.
</P>
<P>
As a separate city under plan with decision-making power
directly granted by the central government, Chongqing has been
separated with Sichuan in economic goals and budget, which makes
it easy to tackle some knotty problems.
</P>
<P>
When Chongqing becomes a municipality, the area under its
jurisdiction will be 82,000 sq km with a population of 30 million,
the largest city in China.
</P>
<P>
With a history of more than 3,000 years, Chongqing was opened
as a trade port in 1891 and officially became a city in 1929. It
was a political and cultural center of southwestern China and
designated as a municipality directly under central government in
the post-liberation years in early 1950s. Afterwards, it was
changed into a city directly under the jurisdiction of the
provincial government in 1954. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
