<HEADLINE> Tour Party Robbed In Sri Lanka's Game Sanctuary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 6 (Xinhua) -- A tour party including two British
tourists were robbed Wednesday by an armed group in camouflage
uniforms who also hijacked their vehicle in Sri Lanka's national
game sanctuary Yala in the deep south, according to police sources
today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the tour party had been accosted by seven
armed men who ordered them to alight from their vehicle. When they
showed reluctance the gang had threatened to shoot them.
</P>
<P>
The occupants had then alighted and handed over the vehicle to
the gang and proceeded to a nearby army camp and reported the
incident.
</P>
<P>
The vehicle, a jeep, was later found abandoned and set on fire
where it had got stuck in the mud in a stream in the sanctuary,
they said.
</P>
<P>
A few weeks ago, a group of men similarly clad had threatened
some fishermen and stolen their provisions near the sanctuary.
</P>
<P>
The sources suspect that the gang is a group of Tamil rebel
cadres who had penetrated the sanctuary from the North of the
country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
