<HEADLINE> Brazil Doubles Soybean Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian exports of
soybeans will double this year to reach seven million tons, the
biggest volume of exports in the history of this country.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the Brazilian Association of Vegetable Oil
Industries said the increase in the production is due to the
elimination of a tax on the movement of goods and services which
affected some products including soybeans.
</P>
<P>
Brazil is the second largest producer of soybeans in the world
and one of the most important exporters.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Brazil earned more than two billion U.S. dollars
from exports of soybeans and by-products. 
