<HEADLINE> Tianjin's Successful Foreign Technology Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin, the third largest
centrally-administered municipality in China, has made big
progress in scientific and technological exchange and cooperation
with foreign countries,
</P>
<P>
Tianjin cooperated with foreign governments in 29 scientific
and technological projects in 1996, covering agriculture,
industry, health care and environment protection.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 1,000 foreign experts were invited to Tianjin last year
to advise locals in the fields of machinery, electronics,
textiles, light industry, agriculture, environment protection as
well as urban construction.
</P>
<P>
Since 1995 Tianjin has embarked on a project to promote applied
technology by expanding foreign technology exchange.
</P>
<P>
The project has enabled the city to sign 33 technology
contracts with more than 20 countries and regions, with contracted
overseas funds surpassing 32 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Such exchange and cooperation are expected to drive local
science and technology development forward.
</P>
<P>
In 1996 Tianjin signed 32 technology-export contracts, valued
at 150 million US dollars, a 57 percent rise from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
