<DOCNO> XIE19970306.0286 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chile Promotes Exports To Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Chilean exports to Russia jumped
to 120 million U.S. dollars in 1996, six times the figure in
1993.
</P>
<P>
The trade volume between the two countries totalled 146
million dollars last year, of which Chilean imports from Russia
amounted to only 26.5 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Hector Casanueva, director of the Export Promotion Department
of the Foreign Ministry, said the Russian market is a big one
consisting of 150 million people and is the door to all the
republics that are members of the former Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
He said his department hopes to maintain an aggressive policy
toward emerging markets this year.
</P>
<P>
To this end, trade missions will be sent to Croatia, Ukraine
and Russia when Foreign Minister Jose Miguel Insulza visits these
countries starting in late March, he said.
</P>
<P>
During his tour, Insulza will attend in Russia on March 28 the
inauguration of the "Corporation Tres Hontes" soft drink plant,
the first Chilean industrial company to operate in that country.
</P>
<P>
The company reportedly has also invested 30 million dollars in
Lithuania where products are being made for the Russian market.
</P>
<P>
Osvaldo Droppelman, president of the Chilean-Russian Chamber of
Commerce, announced that the two countries will sign an agreement
on cooperation in Moscow at the end of this month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
