<HEADLINE> Muslim Rebels Surrender to Philippine Army </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 6 (Xinhua) -- A group of the Moro Islamic
Liberation Front (MILF) guerrillas have surrendered to the
Philippines Army in Labangan town in Zambaoanga del Sur in the
southern Philippines, the local newspaper Manila Bulletin said
today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 64 MILF fighters led by Commander Ananggo Sumandar
surrendered last week to the 57th Infantry Battalion under the 1st
Infantry Division, the paper quoted a military report as saying.
</P>
<P>
The MILF rebels also turned over to Army authorities high
powered guns, including 15 M-14 rifles, two AK-47 assault rifles
and a Thompson submachine gun.
</P>
<P>
Major General Romeo Pdiernos of the 1st Infantry Division said
he expected more MILF rebels would surrender to government forces
in view of the ongoing peace negotiations between the government
and the MILF.
</P>
<P>
The MILF, a breakaway group of the larger Moro National
Liberation Front (MNLF), has refused to accept a peace deal
concluded between the MNLF and the government but wanted separate
peace talks with Manila.
</P>
<P>
The MILF and the government began their long-delayed
exploratory peace talks on January 9 but the second round of the
talks have been stalled by sporadic fighting between the two
sides.
</P>
<P>
The two sides made some progress during their low-level
negotiations late last month on how to monitor the implementation
of a limited regional ceasefire agreement in Buldon town in
Maguindanao province in Mindanao island.
</P>
<P>
Encouraged by the progress, both the MILF and the government
expressed optimism about the conclusion of a comprehensive
agreement ending hostilities between the two sides in the southern
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
But the two sides are still wide apart on their talking points
in the stalled exploratory peace talks which will be resumed in
April.
</P>
<P>
The MILF is currently the largest anti-government group in the
country, with an estimated membership of more than 12,000.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
