<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy PM Pleased with WTO Successes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi
today praised the recent successes of the World Trade Organization
(WTO) in liberalizing trade in information technology and
telecommunications services.
</P>
<P>
Prodi made the remarks when he met with WTO Director-General
Renato Ruggiero, who is a former Italian Foreign Trade Minister.
</P>
<P>
Ruggiero briefed Prodi on his coming tasks, with top priority
going to starting talks on liberalizing financial services.
</P>
<P>
He also focused on prospects of integrating developing
countries into the WTO system and the possibility of new members
for the organization.
</P>
<P>
Prodi told Ruggiero of the Italian government's appreciation of
his hard work in expanding free trade and reiterated Italy's full
support for these efforts.
</P>
<P>
``The liberalization of world trade in goods and services and
the promotion of investments constitute a formidable instrument
for economic development, increased employment, and the wellbeing
of the people of the whole world,'' the Italian government said.
</P>
</TEXT>
