<HEADLINE> China Develops New Oil Pumps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- A new highly efficient oil pump
has just been developed in China to replace the floating beam
pumps, which are still widely used but are not very efficient and
are energy consuming.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the new oil pumps have a larger capacity than
the floating beam pumps and are more effective, and can be used
for a longer time. An added benefit is that they can be examined
or repaired without stopping the machine.
</P>
<P>
Li Hengguang, manager of Succeed Hi-tech Testing Form Complied
Co., Ltd, which developed the new design, said that feedback from
major Chinese oilfields indicates that the 100 machines now in use
are doing well.
</P>
<P>
He said that oil wells needn't alter anything if the oilfields
want to use the new machine.  
</P>
</TEXT>
