<HEADLINE> Sichuan Upgrading Old Highway Sections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 40 sections of highway have
been upgraded in southwest China's Sichuan Province since last
year.
</P>
<P>
Most of the roadways, in disrepair for many years, are located
along winding and steep mountainsides, or in mountainous areas,
causing frequent traffic accidents.
</P>
<P>
Work is continuing for another 16 sections, the provincial
transportation authorities said, adding that the capital city of
Chengdu is checking other roads in need of fixing.
</P>
<P>
The Sichuan provincial government has decided to carry out
repair work on 100 more old highway sections and ports this year,
according to the authorities.  
