<HEADLINE> Expressway Construction Gaining Momentum In Hebei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, March 6 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei Province
is constructing 677 km of expressways, after building the third
longest expressway in China.
</P>
<P>
The province, which nearly surrounds the national capital
Beijing, has 276 km of expressways in use. The roads link
Shijiazhuang, the provincial capital, to Beijing, Tianjin and
major cities in nearby Shanxi and Henan provinces.
</P>
<P>
Hebei, known for its ambitious economic take-off, is going to
invest 22.7 billion yuan to build 1,058 km more of expressways in
the period from 1996-2000.  
