<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 5 (Xinhua) -- European Cup holders Juventus
recovered from one goal deficit to draw 1-1 with Rosenborg in
their Champions League quarter-final on Wednesday night in
Trondheim, Norway.
</P>
<P>
Juventus, without either of the strikers who have started in
their European competitions, Alessandro Del Piero and Croatian
Alen Boksic, struggled in the first half. But they began to
dominate after halftime.
</P>
<P>
Anyway, the home team opened the scoring in the 51 minutes
through Trond Soltvedt while the Italian side pulled back just two
minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Christian Vieri scored the equaliser, and also created his
teams' first chance in the match. He broke through the Norwegian
defence on the left side and shot fiercely just wide of the post.
</P>
<P>
Juventus had many chances for the second goal, which could make
it easier for their Turin match in two weeks, but they failed to
grasp the chances.
</P>
<P>
However, coach Marcello Lippi said: "We had chances to win, but
I'm happy enough with the result."
</P>
<P>
Rosenborg, who earned their place in the last eight by beating
AC Milan 2-1 at San Siro, showed some world-class ball skills, but
they were lack of finishing. 
</P>
