<HEADLINE> Third Plenary Meeting of NPC Fifth Session Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 6 (Xinhua) -- The Fifth Session of the Eighth
National People's Congress (NPC), China's top legislature,
convened its third plenary meeting today to review two draft laws
-- draft amendments to the criminal law and a draft national
defence law -- and other legislative affairs.
</P>
<P>
Chen Muhua, vice-chairperson of the NPC Standing Committee and
an executive chairman of the NPC Fifth Session, presided over today's
session.
</P>
<P>
Wang Hanbin, vice-chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, made
explanations on draft amendments to the criminal law.
</P>
<P>
He said revision of the country's 17-year-old criminal code
will represent a major step forward in improving the country's
socialist legal system.
</P>
<P>
Chi Haotian, vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission,
state councillor and minister of national defence, will explain the
draft national defence law at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
A draft decision on matters of electing deputies to the Ninth NPC
and draft methods for electing Hong Kong deputies to the Ninth
NPC will be submitted to the NPC for deliberation today, according
to the agenda.
</P>
<P>
A motion put forward by the State Council on establishing
Chongqing city in Sichuan province as a municipality directly
under the central government will also be presented at today's
meeting. State Councillor Li Guixian will explain the motion at
the meeting. 
</P>
