<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.N. Report: Peru Remains Leading Producer of Coca Leaves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Peru continues to be the world's
principal producer of coca leaves, says an annual report by the
United Nations international supervisory board of narcotic
substances.
</P>
<P>
The report, published here today, says that the efforts to
eradicate coca shrubs in Peru are centered almost exclusively on
seedlings, and urges that the Peruvian government should also
eradicate mature plants.
</P>
<P>
It says that coca paste base is made mainly in Peru and
Bolivia, where the illegal production of hydrochloride of cocaine
has also increased.
</P>
<P>
A considerable part of coca paste produced in Peru is sent to
Colombia and processed into cocaine.
</P>
<P>
The international supervisory board of narcotic substances also
expresses satisfaction that the authorities in Peru, Bolivia,
Colombia, Ecuador and Venezuela agreed in June 1996 to create an
Andean information service for combating illegal drugs.
</P>
<P>
It notes that South America is the only region that supplies
cocaine to other regions of the world, especially to the United
States and European countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
