<HEADLINE> EC Adopts Action Plan on Satellite Communication </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission (EC)
adopted today an Action Plan which aims to improve significantly
the European Union's role in the provision of global satellite
communications services and applications.
</P>
<P>
The actions aim to focus the European industrial potential on
the new generation of global satellite systems, advanced services
and innovative applications which meet key user requirements in
the global Information Society, such as personal mobility, access
to the broadband evolution of Internet, fast response times, and
global connectivity.
</P>
<P>
The commission said in the Action Plan that global satellite
infrastructures will become a critical part of the world's
economic system.
</P>
<P>
"As a result," it said, "a strong and coherent satellite
communications industry and services sector is of high economic
and political importance for Europe."
</P>
<P>
The commission acknowledged that the European satellite
equipment and service industry was not well placed to achieve the
position in the commercial space sector needed to support the EU's
ambitions to remain a major player in this sector.
</P>
<P>
It warned that should Europe not react in a coordinated manner,
there is a high risk from being kept out of the most promising
market of service and equipment.
</P>
<P>
"In the long run this would have consequences on the European
position in launching services," it said.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, the revenues generated in the various
market segments (satellite, terminals and services) are expected
to reach 400 billion US dollars over the next 10 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
