<HEADLINE> Coffee Soars to New Highs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 5 (Xinhua) -- Coffee futures prices soared to
new highs in New York for a third day today after workers at
Brazil's third-largest port continued their strike that could
delay shipments.
</P>
<P>
Green arabica coffee for May delivery soared 5.40 cents to
2.006 U.S. dollars a pound; March coffee soared as high as 2.275
U.S. dollars a pound before settling at 2.198 U.S. dollars, up
8.10 cents. That was the highest settlement since September 28,
1994.
</P>
<P>
Brazil is the world's largest coffee exporter.
</P>
<P>
Other countries in January stepped up their exports of arabica
coffee following the price increases, the London-based
International Coffee Organization reported. That leaves little
coffee to be shipped now, analysts said. 
</P>
