<HEADLINE> UAE Calls for Support to Palestinian Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, March 5 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates (UAE)
today called for international efforts to help Palestinian
refugees to return to their homes, the UAE's official news
agency Wam reported.
</P>
<P>
International community should assume its responsibilities
toward Palestinian refugees who are living in the areas
controlled by the Palestinian National Authority, Jordan, Syria
and Lebanon, and help them gain the right of returning to their
homelands, Wam quoted UAE's Minister of Finance and Industry
Ahmad Hamid Taer as saying.
</P>
<P>
The minister made the remarks during his meeting with Peter
Hansen, Commissioner General of United Nation Relief and Works
Agency For Palestine Refugees in the Near East (UNRWA) who is
visiting the UAE.
</P>
<P>
The minister called for ending the sufferings of Palestinian
refugees, saying international community should support the
Palestinians not only by financial efforts, but also through
moves to help them enjoy the right of returning to their
homelands, Wam said.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that some 3.35 million Palestinian refugees
depending on UNRWA services will face serious cutback in services
unless the UNRWA is able to mobilize 50 to 60 million
U.S. dollars to meet its budget deficit in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Hansen's visit to the UAE is part of his efforts to gain
finaccial support from donor countries in the Gulf.
</P>
<P>
The UNWRA has been providing free education, health, relief
and social services to registered Palestinian refugees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
